OPERCULUM (
Fig. 19
). Thin, chitinous, orange, almost circular with central nucleus, the latter without peg or peg-like modification.

MALE GENITALIA (
Fig. 17C–E
). Testis starting at least one whorl below apex, comprising ca 0.25 whorls, reaching stomach; prostate kidney shaped; penis massive, trapezoidal, with rounded lobe on left side, small, brown, probably chitinous stylet anterior right near penial opening.
